A prominent politician and member of the Legislature is expected to appear in the Seshego Magistrate s Court tomorrow (Wednesday) on a charge of assault. Provincial Police Spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe confirmed that the politician was arrested yesterday (Monday) and released on warning. This follows an alleged domestic incident in Seshego last weekend. It is alleged that the suspect was involved in the reported assault of family members following an apparent dispute over his late grandparents house. Story: RC Myburgh &gt;&gt;rc.observer@gmail.com